# Filament layer

Path: `app/Filament/{BC}/Resources/...` — code folders follow **bounded context**.

Navigation (`$navigationGroup`) is grouped by **manager UX semantics**, not by BC folder names.
Code stays in its BC; only the sidebar group label may cluster related resources.

Canonical sidebar groups (order in `AdminPanelProvider`):

| Group | Resources |
|-------|-----------|
| Клиенты | Clients (CRM), Reviews moderation (Feedback) |
| Заказы | Orders, Delivery |
| Оборудование | Equipment |
| Склад | Stock |
| Финансы | Payments, Cash operations |
| Сотрудники | Staff users (Identity) |

## Architecture

### Allowed

- Read/list/view via Eloquent Infrastructure models
- Direct Eloquent create/update/delete **only** for catalogs without domain logic (e.g. staff `User`)
- Domain mutations via Application Command handlers (actions / custom create flows)
- `DomainResource` for aggregates; `CatalogResource` for catalogs

### Forbidden

- Direct Eloquent writes for aggregates with domain invariants (`Order`, `ProductionTask`, `Client`, stock, payments, …)
- Calling another BC’s Application handlers from a Filament resource
- Restoring old Filament/admin as-was from the previous codebase
- Instructional / meta hints (`helperText`, hints, placeholders) that explain **how the UI works** instead of the field meaning — e.g. «Список частей только для просмотра. Добавление — кнопками сверху.»

```php
// ❌ BAD — подсказка про механику интерфейса
Repeater::make('components_display')
    ->helperText('Список частей только для просмотра. Добавление — кнопками сверху.');

// ✅ GOOD — без такой подсказки; при необходимости короткий domain-смысл поля
TextInput::make('notes')->label('Заметки');
```

## UI language — Russian only

All **user-facing** Filament copy is Russian: navigation groups/labels, `$modelLabel` / `$pluralModelLabel` / `$navigationLabel`, column labels, form labels, placeholders, hints, helper text, action labels, notifications, empty states, section headings.

```php
// ❌ BAD
protected static ?string $navigationGroup = 'CRM';
protected static ?string $modelLabel = 'Client';
Action::make('registerClient')->label('Register client');

// ✅ GOOD
protected static ?string $navigationGroup = 'Клиенты';
protected static ?string $modelLabel = 'Клиент';
Action::make('registerClient')->label('Зарегистрировать клиента');
```

Code identifiers stay English (see naming rule). Only UI strings are Russian.

## Phone input mask

Every phone `TextInput` / form field in Filament **must** use:

```text
+7 (999) 999-99-99
```

Visual target matches the public site (`+7 (___) ___-__-__`), but the **mask engine is different**.

| Layer | Library | Digit wildcard | Phone mask |
|-------|---------|----------------|------------|
| Public Vue (`resources/js`) | maska (`data-maska`) | `#` | `+7 (###) ###-##-##` |
| Filament (`app/Filament`) | Alpine Mask (`->mask()`) | `9` | `+7 (999) 999-99-99` |

Filament `TextInput::mask()` is Alpine.js Mask. Alpine wildcards:

- `9` — digit only
- `a` — letter only
- `*` — any character
- `#` — **not** a digit wildcard; treated as a literal `#`

**Never** copy-paste the Vue/maska pattern into Filament.

```php
// ❌ BAD — maska / public-site syntax; Alpine treats # as literal character
TextInput::make('phone')
    ->mask('+7 (###) ###-##-##');

// ❌ BAD — no mask / wrong digit token
TextInput::make('phone')->tel()->required();

// ✅ GOOD — Alpine digit wildcard is 9; telRegex must match the mask
// (default Filament tel regex rejects parentheses/spaces in +7 (999) 999-99-99)
TextInput::make('phone')
    ->label('Телефон')
    ->tel()
    ->telRegex('/^\+7 \(\d{3}\) \d{3}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/')
    ->mask('+7 (999) 999-99-99')
    ->placeholder('+7 (___) ___-__-__')
    ->required();
```
